==English==

===Noun===
'''camber'''
# the [[slightly]] [[convex]] [[surface]] of a [[road]], [[ship]]'s [[deck]] etc
# the [[slope]] of a [[curved]] road, such that the [[outside]] is higher than the [[inside]]
# an [[alignment]] of the [[wheel]]s of a road [[vehicle]] with positive camber signifying that the wheels are [[closer]] [[together]] at the [[bottom]] than at the [[top]]
# the curvature of an [[airfoil]]
#{{nautical}} a small [[enclosed]] [[dock]] in which [[timber]] for [[mast]]s etc is kept to [[weather]]

===Intransitive verb===
'''to camber'''
# to curve upwards in the middle

